'''Howard G. Kazanjian''' is a former Vice President of [[Lucasfilm]] and producer of [[Star Wars: Episode VI Return of the Jedi|''Return of the Jedi'']]. Kazanjian also produced for [[George Lucas]] on ''Raiders of the Lost Ark'', and was an uncredited producer on [[Star Wars: Episode V The Empire Strikes Back|''The Empire Strikes Back'']].

{{Stub}}

==Biography==
Howard Kazanjian attended the [[Wikipedia:University of Southern California|University of Southern California]] alongside [[George Lucas]]. They became not only Delta Kappa Alpha cinema fraternity brothers but also longstanding friends. During those college years, Kazanjian and Lucas met their respective future wives and the couples would often double date. Kazanjian went on to work with filmmakers such as [[Wikipedia:Alfred Hitchcock|Alfred Hitchcock]], [[Wikipedia:Elia Kazan|Elia Kazan]], [[Wikipedia:Sam Peckinpah|Sam Peckinpah]], and [[Wikipedia:Robert Wise|Robert Wise]].<ref name="Creative Armenia" />

After Lucas' initial [[Star Wars: Episode IV A New Hope|''Star Wars'']] film was released in [[1977]] and set up [[Lucasfilm]], Kazanjian was intimately involved in the company's day-to-day strategic and practical operation as its Vice President of Production, a role that he maintained until around 1984-1985. Since Lucas had quit the [[Wikipedia:Directors Guild of America|Directors Guild of America]] over ''Star Wars''{{'}} opening titles and did not want to return to directing, he had to hire film directors outside the Hollywood studio system for the rest of the [[original trilogy]]. Most American directors were thereby excluded, including Lucas' friends such as [[Steven Spielberg]].<ref name="Creative Armenia" /> Lucas invited [[Irvin Kershner]] to direct [[Star Wars: Episode V The Empire Strikes Back|''The Empire Strikes Back'']] and later [[David Lynch]] and [[Wikipedia:David Cronenberg|David Cronenberg]] for [[Star Wars: Episode VI Return of the Jedi|''Return of the Jedi'']].<ref name="Lynch">{{YouTube|video=EJQ4vCu-S0U|text=David Lynch Meets George Lucas|channel=channel/UCddKc3pzpVPLYdKf39ulrpQ|name=hudsonunionsociety|archivedate=20211119223219}}</ref>

Cronenberg declined and Lynch took on the job for one day, dropping the project when he realized that he could not understand the story and urged Lucas to direct his own film.<ref name="Lynch" /> Kazanjian recalled that Lynch was wanting to include neither [[John Williams]] nor [[Ben Burtt]] for music and sound design if he was director; Lynch wanted to focus on his [[Wikipedia:Dune (1984 film)|''Dune'']] film, which was eventually made and released in 1984. Although Lynch was his first choice, Lucas hired his second choice, [[Richard Marquand]], to direct ''Return of the Jedi'' instead, with Kazanjian serving as producer.<ref name="Creative Armenia" />

